INSERT INTO public.vacancy VALUES ('c99021a5-8fa1-48f7-9bef-cdab2580504d', 'Stage-opdracht - HBO - Informatica. Common Services Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Premium 30+ dagen geleden Thales In fast changing markets, customers worldwide rely on Thales. Thales is a business where brilliant people from all over the world come together to share ideas and inspire each other. In aerospace, transportation, defence, security and space, our architects design innovative solutions that make our tomorrow''s possible. Soort opdracht: Stage-opdracht Niveau: HBO Studierichting(en): Informatica/Computer Science Titel van de opdracht: Common Services About us In the Netherlands, where 2100 employees are based, we are located in four cities: Huizen, Delft, Eindhoven and Hengelo (HQ). Together with an extensive ecosystem of knowledge partners, customers and suppliers, we work on radars for naval vessels, cyber security solutions, transportation systems, communication equipment for land forces, cryogenic cooling solutions and research & development for radar tech (in collaboration with TU Delft). The software department of the Application Engineering cluster is responsible for the software development in Combat Management and Radar- and Optical sensors for worldwide navies- and defense systems. The work is performed in multi-disciplinary agile teams with specialists in software/system/test engineering and functional design. About the assignment Within the software department, we have the desire to deliver new features to market even faster. For this, more loosely coupled systems and automated deployments are necessary. Loosely coupled systems benefit from a microservice architecture together with OS virtualisation (Kubernetes). There are several assignments available that are related to services that are common for different part of our systems. Services like time data, meteo data, chart service and parameter service are ready to become loosely coupled (micro)