INSERT INTO public.vacancy VALUES ('c0ebc233-c453-43fd-8a88-8f501201d88f', 'Senior Full Stack Engineer Loyalty platform Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Premium 30+ dagen geleden ING Senior Full Stack Engineer Loyalty platform We are looking for an experienced full stack engineer who will build the platform for our Loyalty program and offer the best user experience for our customers. We look for an engineer with modern day engineering skills and competences like an eye for innovation, creativity, attention to details and communication. Who we are We are Squad Loyalty and we build and maintain the ING Points Shop. This is a full grown web shop where ING customers can get discounts with loyalty points for all kind of products or vouchers. The platform consists of the front-end web shop, the back-end API‚Äôs (and datastores) that handle the stock in the warehouse, placing orders, shipping products and handling returns. We are continuously improving these processes by monitoring bottlenecks and asking customers for feedback. Who you are You are a highly motivated engineer who likes to work in a multidisciplinary team of engineers and business colleagues. Next to your work in the squad, you also like to contribute to the mastery of other engineers and improve the way of work within ING. You are a senior full stack engineer with more than 5 years‚Äô experience in Java back-end development and 3 years‚Äô experience in front-end development. As a Java developer you have experience with Java 8 or higher, Spring (Boot) and back-end tooling like Maven, Jenkins, Git, Sonar and with the Tomcat server. On the front-end part you have experience with JavaScript, HTML and CSS, and with NPM and Bower. You also have experience or knowledge of web component development and lit-html. Experience with OPS related activities like deployments and monitoring is a huge plus. You have experience with applying (back-end) design patterns and architecture. You have great analytical skills and conceptual understanding. You are able to quickly understand new technical concepts and technology and you have a strong interest in, and vision of, the latest trends in software development and technology. You have experience with giving presentations and workshops, and in general have strong communication skills that enable you to explain complex technical concepts to non-techies. Your English in speaking and writing is fluent and you are a team player who likes to join the social events of the squad and ING organisation. What we offer A full-time position (40h per week) in a highly challenging environment with bleeding edge technology and concepts. Modern agile international organization and really nice colleagues. An excellent salary, 13th month and free public transportation. And the best place to grow your technical capabilities and personal competences. Type vacature: Intern Vaardigheden Er is geen minimale opleiding vereist Voor deze functie is er geen minimale werkervaring vereist ICT Engineer Java Developer Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Of solliciteer later Dit is geen correct e-mailadres. Vul a.u.b. alle velden in. Bewijs dat je geen robot bent. Er is iets misgegaan bij het versturen van de e-mail. Probeer het nog eens. Je e-mail is verzonden. Jouw e-mailadres Doorsturen', 'Jobbird', NULL, '', '2020-09-16 00:00:00', NULL, 'Senior Full Stack Engineer Loyalty platform', NULL, 'https://www.jobbird.com/nl/vacature/10183510-senior-full-stack-engineer-loyalty-platform');
INSERT INTO public.vacancy VALUES ('b89bfce3-6740-41a3-b906-7acddb1f93f0', 'SOFTWARE ENGINEER C++ Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Premium 30+ dagen geleden Thales In fast changing markets, customers worldwide rely on Thales. Thales is a business where brilliant people from all over the world come together to share ideas and inspire each other. In aerospace, transportation, defence, security and space, our architects design innovative solutions that make our tomorrow''s possible. SOFTWARE ENGINEER C++ To strengthen our Thales (Hengelo) team within the cluster Above Water Warfare (AWW) Fire Control Systems (FCS), we are looking for enthusiastic and motivated SOFTWARE ENGINEERS C++ with a passion for technology and the ambition to pursue a career in a high-tech environment. About the job As a Software Engineer you work in a multidisciplinary and self-organizing Agile-Scrum team. In addition to software product development, our teams are fully responsible for a various aspects such as requirements analysis, design, architecture, testing, validation and regular product demonstrations. The use of high-tech techniques and software development methods is important. The Fire Control System product development is based both on Java and C++ and is supported by a modern development environment. Large parts of the Missile Fire Control and Gun Fire Control domains are based on the C++ technology stack. The Above Water Warfare Fire Control System (AWW-FCS) protects ships and other units from above-water threats, which are becoming faster, smarter and more complex. To this end, it uses Thales'' next-generation dual-band radar suite, which integrates an Active Phased-Array Radar (APAR) in the X-band with a Sea Master 400 radar in the S-band Anti-ship missiles go three to five times faster than sound with increasingly complex behavior. When several of these threats come up against them simultaneously, it becomes increasingly difficult for human operators to take efficient and effective protection measures. The AWW-FCS provides the necessary information to make the right decision within seconds. With a combination of a new generation of sensors and an intelligent Fire Control System, it continuously assesses which methods are best suited to engage the detected threat. A Fire Control System combines the radar and the intelligent algorithm which is designed to assist a ranged weapon system in targeting, tracking and hitting its target. About you Are you passionate about technology and would you like to work on the high-tech architecture of Naval Fire Control Systems? If so, you are the person we are looking for. You are a talented and experienced C++ Software Engineer who likes to cooperate in the design and development of software solutions within our complex Naval domain. You have a solid background in software development using modern development tools and methods. You are capable of rapidly mastering new domains and techniques. You graduated at HBO or WO level in the field of Information or Computer Science. As a person, you are creative, open and flexible and able to operate as an enthusiastic team player. In addition, you are result-oriented, show initiative and able to communicate clearly. An excellent command of the Dutch and English languages, both spoken and written, is essential in order to perform well in this role. Knowledge of and experience with the following tools and techniques are important: ‚Ä¢ Agile/Scrum software development ‚Ä¢ C++, CMake, real-time software development ‚Ä¢ Continuous Integration & Delivery ‚Ä¢ Jenkins, Nexus, Maven, GIT, BitBucket ‚Ä¢ Unit Testing, Test Automation, Google-Test ‚Ä¢ MatLab, SimuLink (pr√©) In addition, we will offer you the opportunity to further your career within Thales'' high-tech environment. You could become one of our future System Engineers, with extensive domain expertise and a broad view on systems. Or if you are an excellent organiser, you may find that a career path in the field of Agile ScrumMaster or Project Lead fits your profile. What''s in it for you Become part of a great team in a high tech, innovative international organization (International) opportunities for growth in tech-, management- and commercial roles Attention for personal development and own initiative A nice workplace in a modern building, where we value a good work-life balance and flexibility 40 leave days per year, travel expenses and a flexible benefits √† la carte package with options like purchase/sale of leave hours, internet costs, bicycle plan, company fitness, trade union contribution or relocation costs Interested? Apply now! Click on the button below to upload your profile and show your interest. To ensure that we are a good match, we can ask you to participate in an assessment. At Thales we provide CAREERS and not only jobs. With Thales employing 80,000 employees in 68 countries our mobility policy enables thousands of employees each year to develop their careers at home and abroad, in their existing areas of expertise or by branching out into new fields. Together we believe that embracing flexibility is a smarter way of working. Great journeys start here, apply now! Type vacature: Intern Vaardigheden Er is geen minimale opleiding vereist Voor deze functie is er geen minimale werkervaring vereist ICT Engineer Java Software engineer Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Of solliciteer later Dit is geen correct e-mailadres. Vul a.u.b. alle velden in. Bewijs dat je geen robot bent. Er is iets misgegaan bij het versturen van de e-mail. Probeer het nog eens. Je e-mail is verzonden. Jouw e-mailadres Doorsturen', 'Jobbird', NULL, '', '2020-09-16 00:00:00', NULL, 'SOFTWARE ENGINEER C++', NULL, 'https://www.jobbird.com/nl/vacature/10441552-software-engineer-c');
INSERT INTO public.vacancy VALUES ('c9362c39-db5e-4abe-aa7c-ba2bd30b01ca', '<p>For a company focusing on high volume data movement/replication I am looking for a software engineer (C/C++).</p>
