INSERT INTO public.vacancy VALUES ('cb79cbf4-874e-4180-ba0b-e384470f81d2', 'Afstudeeropdracht - HBO/WO - Computer Science. GIT Based localization Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Premium 30+ dagen geleden Thales In fast changing markets, customers worldwide rely on Thales. Thales is a business where brilliant people from all over the world come together to share ideas and inspire each other. In aerospace, transportation, defence, security and space, our architects design innovative solutions that make our tomorrow''s possible. Soort opdracht: Afstudeeropdracht Niveau: HBO/WO Studierichting(en): Computer Science Titel van de opdracht: GIT based localization About us In the Netherlands, where 2100 employees are based, we are located in four cities: Huizen, Delft, Eindhoven and Hengelo (HQ). Together with an extensive ecosystem of knowledge partners, customers and suppliers, we work on radars for naval vessels, cyber security solutions, transportation systems, communication equipment for land forces, cryogenic cooling solutions and research & development for radar tech (in collaboration with TU Delft). The software department of the Application Engineering cluster is responsible for the software development in Combat Management and Radar- and Optical sensors for worldwide navies- and defense systems. The work is performed in multi-disciplinary agile teams with specialists in software/system/test engineering and functional design. About the assignment The Tacticos Combat Management system is used by customers all over the world and has therefore built-in multi language support. External tooling is used by both software engineers and translators to provide localized values for the entire product. The tool has limitations regarding traceability and maintenance. As a graduate you will be investigating whether a version control system (GIT) based application could replace the current localization tooling. You will investigate the way GIT versioning and branching can help to get a better insight in the current state and history of Tacticos‚Äô localization. You will develop an application on which both software developers and translators can cooperate to localize the Tacticos product. Affinity GIT, Java, JavaFX, User Interface Thales offers‚Ä¶ An interesting internship or graduation assignment in an international high tech environment An open and flexible working environment An excellent internship allowance Its own student association where you can participate in educational and fun activities. Interested? Direct solliciteren? Gebruik dan je eigen, persoonlijke profiel om jouw interesse aan ons kenbaar te maken en kies voor ‚ÄòApply now‚Äô. Would you like to apply directly? Then click on the button ‚ÄòApply now‚Äô to show your interest. Please keep in mind that we can only consider students who are enrolled at a school during the whole internship period for our internships and graduation assignments. At Thales we provide CAREERS and not only jobs. With Thales employing 80,000 employees in 68 countries our mobility policy enables thousands of employees each year to develop their careers at home and abroad, in their existing areas of expertise or by branching out into new fields. Together we believe that embracing flexibility is a smarter way of working. Great journeys start here, apply now! Type vacature: Intern Vaardigheden Er is geen minimale opleiding vereist Voor deze functie is er geen minimale werkervaring vereist ICT Java Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Of solliciteer later Dit is geen correct e-mailadres. Vul a.u.b. alle velden in. Bewijs dat je geen robot bent. Er is iets misgegaan bij het versturen van de e-mail. Probeer het nog eens. Je e-mail is verzonden. Jouw e-mailadres Doorsturen', 'Jobbird', NULL, '', '2020-09-16 00:00:00', NULL, 'Afstudeeropdracht - HBO/WO - Computer Science. GIT Based localization', NULL, 'https://www.jobbird.com/nl/vacature/9984544-afstudeeropdracht-hbo-wo-computer-science-git-based-localization');
INSERT INTO public.vacancy VALUES ('cf8e2537-c988-473b-887b-2b434f5dcbd4', 'CTO / Tech Lead (design/development) (ITP7821) (MediorSenior) in Nijmegen (bij Zaanstad) Solliciteer Solliciteer op de website van de werkgever Zaandam 15 september ITProgrammeur.com Je bij Academic en bezit kennis over frontend, java, javascript en mag sowieso Teamuitjes, Onkostenvergoeding, Ontwikkelingsmogelijkheden verwachten en werkniveau van een Lead of Medior of Senior en hebt het HBO of WO of MBO denkniveau Functie: CTO / Tech Lead (design/development) (ITP7821) Start: 15-9-2020, 36 uur per week Periode: 9 mnd+ Omgeving: Amsterdam Omschrijving: For our client in Amsterdam we are looking for a CTO / Tech Lead (design/development). Can you build a technical structure focussed on scalability and rapid growth? Are you able to transform a functional design into a technical design and build a financial market infrastructure platform with your team? And are you interested in being part of the innovation revolution and contribute to the platform strategy? The team & project Our team builds a digital platform to enable banks to efficiently distribute infrastructure loans to institutional investors and non-bank financial investors. Our platform connects to the existing financial market infrastructure providers that are currently building digital securities networks where bank loans will be administrated on distributed ledgers, opening up new distribution channels and multilateral trading. You will be part of Labs Amsterdam and working in an international and dynamic environment. The customer requirements drive the innovation methodology process (PACE) and you will align with internal sponsors and external partners to validate the vision and build the platform. You will be part of a growing team of 5 people with various value adding backgrounds and focus (Initiative, Commercial, Pilots, Technical). The team will grow as the project requires. Role: As a CTO / Tech Lead you will focus on the technical proposition and set the stage for the technical development of the product. You will propose the technical development strategy by showing the pros and cons of certain choices in architecture and development. to deliver value to the project. This role requires a true all-rounder, as the core responsibilities for the team will be running the infrastructure, writing backend code/scripts, and guide the team in the best in class UX/UI experience for our institutional clients. Additionally you will be responsible for conversing with the technical teams at our international financial market infrastructure partners, making sure that our software infrastructure satisfies safety and reliability requirements, and performing technical due diligence to ensure that we will be able to integrate their functionalities with our platform. Profile: You are an experienced software engineer able to build a technical structure focussed on scalability and rapid growth and you are able to transform an idea into technical reality. Personal profile: - Entrepreneurial spirit - Agile way of working - Customer centric & platform thinking - Energetic, positive mind set, the brainpower to handle complexity and a can-do mentality - Taking ownership and make it happen Professional profile: - 10+ years software development experience and a proven track record in translating functional designs into technical designs - Experience building data heavy B2B platform applications and/or data rooms within the financial services industry - Ability to envision the best in class UX/UI interface for institutional investors - Experience in software architecture, design, (Web) development, security, testing and system integration - Up-to-date knowledge / understanding of DLT technologies like Corda - Experience with 3rd party REST APIs integration and system integration - Experience with at least one OO programming language on the JVM stack, such as Java and at least one functional programming language - Ex