al proposition and set the stage for the technical development of the product. You will propose the technical development strategy by showing the pros and cons of certain choices in architecture and development. to deliver value to the project. This role requires a true all-rounder, as the core responsibilities for the team will be running the infrastructure, writing backend code/scripts, and guide the team in the best in class UX/UI experience for our institutional clients. Additionally you will be responsible for conversing with the technical teams at our international financial market infrastructure partners, making sure that our software infrastructure satisfies safety and reliability requirements, and performing technical due diligence to ensure that we will be able to integrate their functionalities with our platform. Profile: You are an experienced software engineer able to build a technical structure focussed on scalability and rapid growth and you are able to transform an idea into technical reality. Personal profile: - Entrepreneurial spirit - Agile way of working - Customer centric & platform thinking - Energetic, positive mind set, the brainpower to handle complexity and a can-do mentality - Taking ownership and make it happen Professional profile: - 10+ years software development experience and a proven track record in translating functional designs into technical designs - Experience building data heavy B2B platform applications and/or data rooms within the financial services industry - Ability to envision the best in class UX/UI interface for institutional investors - Experience in software architecture, design, (Web) development, security, testing and system integration - Up-to-date knowledge / understanding of DLT technologies like Corda - Experience with 3rd party REST APIs integration and system integration - Experience with at least one OO programming language on the JVM stack, such as Java and at least one functional programming language - Exper